com.hazelcast.cardinality.impl.hyperloglog

Interface HyperLogLog

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DataSerializable, IdentifiedDataSerializable, Versioned
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    HyperLogLogImpl

    public interface HyperLogLog
extends IdentifiedDataSerializable, Versioned
    HyperLogLog is a redundant and highly available distributed data-structure used for cardinality estimation purposes on unique items in significantly sized data cultures. HyperLogLog uses P^2 byte registers for storage and computation. HyperLogLog is an implementation of the two famous papers
    • http://algo.inria.fr/flajolet/Publications/FlFuGaMe07.pdf
    • http://static.googleusercontent.com/media/research.google.com/en//pubs/archive/40671.pdf

    • Method Detail

      • estimate

        long estimate()
        Computes a new estimate for the current status of the registers. If it was previously estimated and never invalidated, then a cached version is used.
        Returns:
        previously cached estimation or a newly computed one.

      • add

        void add(long hash)

      • addAll

        void addAll(long[] hashes)
        Batch aggregation of hash values in the HyperLogLog registers.
        Parameters:
        hashes - the hash values array to aggregate

      • merge

        void merge(HyperLogLog other)
        Merge the two HyperLogLog structures in one. Estimations from both are taken into consideration and the unified estimate should be similar to the distinct union set of the two.
        Parameters:
        other - The second HLL to be merged into this one
